<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-6341"><div id="comment-6341">
<div class="comment_content"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="alignleft avatar"></div>
<div class="alignleft" style="padding-top:5px;"><strong class="comment_author">James Bond</strong><br/><a href="#comment-6341" title="">May 1st, 2009 - 14:06</a></div><div class="clear"></div></div>
<p>How can it be hard to derive Bayes formula if left and right part is essentially the same (A becomes B, B becomes A).</p>
<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/05/visualizing-bayes-theorem/?replytocom=6341#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-6341", "6341", "respond", "119")'>( REPLY )</a></div>
</div><div class="clear"></div></div>
<ul class='children'>
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-6388"><div id="comment-6388">
<div class="comment_content"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="alignleft avatar"></div>
<div class="alignleft" style="padding-top:5px;"><strong class="comment_author"><a href='http://oscarbonilla.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>ob</a></strong><br/><a href="#comment-6388" title="">May 2nd, 2009 - 10:21</a></div><div class="clear"></div></div>
<p>If I understand your question correctly, you&#8217;re saying &#8220;what happens when A and B are the same?&#8221;. In that case, P(AB) = P(A) = P(B), and P(A|B) = 1. Which is saying &#8220;given that event A occurred, what is the probability of event A occurring?&#8221;. It should be pretty obvious that it is 1.</p>
<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/05/visualizing-bayes-theorem/?replytocom=6388#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-6388", "6388", "respond", "119")'>( REPLY )</a></div>
</div><div class="clear"></div></div>
