<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-7399"><div id="comment-7399">
<div class="comment_content"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="alignleft avatar"></div>
<div class="alignleft" style="padding-top:5px;"><strong class="comment_author">jeff wu</strong><br/><a href="#comment-7399" title="">May 28th, 2009 - 15:10</a></div><div class="clear"></div></div>
<p>hmm&#8230; i think the easiest way to understand bayes theorem is to multiply both sides to get..</p>
<p>P(B) P(A|B) = P(A) P(B|A)</p>
<p>both of these are just P(A intersect B) &#8211; probability of A and B is the same as the probability of A times the probability of B given A, or the probability of B times the probability of A given B</p>
<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2009/05/visualizing-bayes-theorem/?replytocom=7399#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-7399", "7399", "respond", "119")'>( REPLY )</a></div>
