	</table></div><h3>Latest Book Review</h3>			<div class="textwidget"><a href="http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5740446-the-return-of-depression-economics-and-the-crisis-of-2008" style="float: left; padding-right: 20px"><img alt="The Return Of Depression Economics And The Crisis Of 2008" border="0" src="http://photo.goodreads.com/books/1267819612m/5740446.jpg" /></a><a href="http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5740446-the-return-of-depression-economics-and-the-crisis-of-2008">The Return Of Depression Economics And The Crisis Of 2008</a> by <a href="http://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1291.Paul_Krugman">Paul Krugman</a><br/>
My rating: <a href="http://www.goodreads.com/review/show/133695278">5 of 5 stars</a><br /><br />
It's hard to find a book about economics that reads like a suspense thriller, but Paul Krugman has achieved precisely that. He is a gifted writer and weaves economic theory, political history, and world events in a thrilling narrative. I finished the book in one night. In a single reading. It's that good.
<br/><br/>
<a href="http://www.goodreads.com/review/list/769807-oscar">View all my reviews</a>
